video.description:
Hi everyone!

Soooooo, let's give this a whirl haha. A really neat idea to think about and try. What if a different band wrote that song? And the extra fun part was the mesh. Trying to keep the original composition and twist it so it still had it's bones but a different band. Hopefully it comes across like that :) Thank you all so much for everything. It means the world. BIG ups for ALWAYS rockin my casbah! 

Xtra Xtra thanks to Leo for hopping on :) He's a fantastic all around musician and a super nice guy! You can check him out here if you'd like: https://www.youtube.com/user/leolego

Best to ya

E

twitter/instagram @BenEllerGuitars
Skype lessons? email BenEllerGuitars@gmail.com 
Original cover video on Ryan Bruce's channel here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EXM2SZr-W_Y

Hey kids! Uncle Ben Eller here, and i'm gonna teach you something cool on Weekend Wankshop 141; a couple weeks ago, my main man Ryan Bruce (aka Fluff) put out a video on his channel with a demo and review of the new Ghost Fantomen signature guitar from Hagstrom! In this video, he did a short cover of Mummy Dust from the Meliora album, and he asked me to lay down a solo!
I based my solo on the original keyboard / keytar solo from the record, with a few added Uncle Ben licks for extra tasty goodness. This is a lot of fun to play, features a variety of techniques, and uses arpeggios in a really cool way to outline chord changes. 
Playing my Suhr Modern Satin into my Kemper Profiler and Avatar 2x12 cabinet. Thanks for watching!
video.title: My Ghost Mummy Dust guitar solo Hagstrom Fantoman demo i did with Fluff Weekend Wankshop 141

Welcome to That Pedal Show! Please subscribe to our channel and visit our store https://www.thatpedalshowstore.com

Life too short for long YouTube videos? Please see the ‘Interesting bits and go-to sections’ information below.


Well, it had to happen eventually. We three have been friends for many years now so it is with great pleasure and much love that we welcome the wonderful, the inimitable, and the very Danish Peter Honoré to the show. 
Peter is known and loved by countless YouTube viewers across the globe from his work on Andertons TV. But he did plenty of interesting, real musician stuff before that too – if you want some history on this Great Dane (woof) watch this: https://youtu.be/CEqKWhR-N-w

In this video Peter talks about his collaboration with Thorpy Pedals on The Dane Overdrive & Booster, as well as entering into a little Tele-off with Dan’s pair of pickin’ planks.

video.description:
Welcome to That Pedal Show and thank you for watching – please subscribe to our channel and visit our store. https://www.thatpedalshowstore.com/

We are also members of Patreon, should you wish to support us in That Pedal Show https://www.patreon.com/thatpedalshow

This is the follow-up to our ‘Boss Metal Zone vs Dan & Mick’   https://youtu.be/l6x6AjsKaMk. 

We’re delighted to have Rabea Massaad (Dorje, Toska, Chapman Guitars, Victory Amplifiers) along as a guest for this video, firstly because he's such a wonderful human, and secondly because he's somebody who actually plays heavy styles properly… unlike Dan & Mick!
https://www.youtube.com/user/rabeaafro

We start by briefly comparing the standard Boss MT-2 Metal Zone to the Analog Man-modded version, before moving on to a run-through some other contemporary high-gain pedals. Bea is not really a gain pedal guy – he prefers using high-gain amps – so we’re interested to hear what he thinks about these. Plus – how good does Dan’s Tele sound as a metal guitar? You might be surprised! 

The pedals today are:

• Boss MT-2 Metal Zone  http://www.bossus.com/products/mt-2/ 
UK & Europe: http://bit.ly/35iLgCF
USA: https://imp.i114863.net/9kQX5

Amps today are a Mesa Lonestar (100-watt mode, clean channel) and a Hamstead Artist 20, running together.

video.description:
Those clever guys at Matrix have been making power amps, speakers & powered speakers for several years & and are the company of choice for many Axe Fx & Kemper owners. Matrix are famous for making amps that are light weight & reliable (& when I say reliable, I mean RELIABLE).
This little amp (called a VB800) is their first foray into making an amp that can be used stand alone, and along with the little 12" cab  we used its about the smallest amp we've ever heard that you could genuinely gig with.

Also check out another cool Matrix video from Andertons at https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JC02YJvwBaM

Want to know more about these amps....
VB800 - http://www.andertons.co.uk/guitar-amp-heads/pid33479/cid689/matrix-amplification-vb800-guitar-amp-head.asp
1x12 Cab - http://www.andertons.co.uk/speaker-cabinets/pid33477/cid690/matrix-amplification-neolight-nl12-compact-1x12-guitar-cab.asp
2x12 Cab - http://www.andertons.co.uk/speaker-cabinets/pid33478/cid690/matrix-amplification-neolight-nl212-compact-2x12-guitar-cab.asp

What did you think then? 

Cheers

Lee & Rob

We know you guys love the David vs Goliath shoot out videos, so here's another one for you. This time we've grabbed the new PRS Floyd Rose loaded guitars - the SE model is a Korean made, relatively affordable guitar & the USA model is a Custom 24 hand made top of the range axe! We give both Floyd Rose systems a full work out, and go through the basic spec of each guitar. Once again we're joined by Aziz Ibrahim.

If you want to find out more about the Floyd Rose loaded SE then go here (there are a few different colours for you to see) - http://www.andertons.co.uk/Products/Products.asp?keyword=prs+se+floyd&type=search&attributeXML0=||||#1399812870114page-1

Full Signal Chain: 
Chapman ML1-7 - Mooer Black Truck - Peavey 6505MH (Clean Channel) - Two Notes Torpedo Live - Focusrite 2i4 - Cubase 6 . There's a little EQ and compression on the guitars but nothing special, just a high/low pass and some notching out at 2k to 4k. 

The Black Truck's distortion can sound WILDLY different depending on how you have it connected to your amp. I'd recommend running it into the front of a clean amp or connecting it using the 4 cable method.

video.description:
Testing out my new 7 string signature model guitar from Chapman Guitars on the court. 

This is the first prototype and the guitar will be in stores by summer of 2019. 

This guitar is essentially the 8 string model I have minus one string and plus a floyd rose. 

Other tweaks: The front and sides are dyed black, slightly shorter scale length, layout of the info on the back of the headstock is a bit different, no locking tuners on the headstock since they're not needed with the locking trem system. This one is prototype 1 so there might be some other small changes before it makes it to stores.

"chronosil" is a tune from my instrumental metal album "The Scene is Dead."

Looks like uke group got really out of hand... normally we just keep to ourselves about the whole vampire who feast on the blood of the innocent to remain immortal thing. But we got a bit carried away and ended up here. Not the first time though, won't be the last.

It's been a while since I've done a banjo cover. And apparently I've been living under a rock or something but I had yet to ever hear a Gojira song. But after stumbling upon this Lost in Vegas video I fell in love with this tune. https://youtu.be/03hxE9O-89k

I learned the song on guitar and must have played through Gojira's "The Heaviest Matter of the Universe" a million times. So it only made sense for me to bring back the banjo and give this a proper barn yard treatment.

Thanks to Gojira, Leo Moracchioli, Lost in Vegas & our crew for the help and inspiration. While we had the barn ready to go I figured we'd make a day of it so Metallica's "Fight Fire with Fire" is next! Cheers!

For this song I am allowed to play only 2 note tritone chords on the guitar tracks. No single notes. 

A tritone is referring to a particular musical interval (how far away two notes are from each other) and is renowned for it's dissonance and harsh feeling of tension. A tritone name refers to the 3 whole tone distance between the two notes.

It's used to great effect in a lot of different genres, but straight up 2 note only tritone chords I most closely associate with Deathcore. And I can't think of anywhere else where it's used anywhere near as often. Particular the band Oceano came to mind while writing this.

It's rumored that the tritone was banned in medieval times, that you could be jailed for using it, that people believed it could summon the devil...  None of which are actually true, but make for a great story that really fits in well with this harsh musical interval.

Here's me chatting about writing this after being thrust into the underworld: https://youtu.be/651DVX5w3Ow

Also pretty much everywhere else music usually is!

The album was made with extended range guitars. 4 tracks of which featuring the 9 string tuned to C# or double drop B. This song was written with the goal of sparingly using the extended low range for particular accents and leaving most of the riffing to regular guitar territory. And if I was able to shred well enough to play Pete's solo it would include all the strings...

The tracks on this album are named after no longer with us metal bands from the Chicago suburbs. The album is dedicated to them and all the other local bands that made up our local metal scene growing up.

video.title: Friends Theme Ska Version w/ Andrew Huang

video.description:
This recording booth looks a lot like an airplane.

See videos early and help them exist on Patreon: http://www.patreon.com/RobScallon

Vocalist played by Jory Caron: https://www.youtube.com/Jory

Screams performed by Austin Dickey: https://www.youtube.com/Dickeyfighter7861
Here's a video of him tracking it: https://youtu.be/ACJVx3pmJDY
And me chatting about that & skydiving: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kqdGzOU9j5Y

I also spliced in a scream from Sarah Longfield (https://www.youtube.com/c/sarahlongfield) which was recorded for our "Payback" cover into a few spots. Jory's screams during the parachute spinning is also actually him.

Song is a condensed version of "Rogue" which is off my new metal album I've been working on for a long time. It will be out... soon. I think.
Song was mixed by Fluff: https://www.youtube.com/user/Fluff191
Drums written by Nick Pierce: https://www.youtube.com/blastbeatshaman

The song did so well on iTunes though they had to take it off to not crash their servers.
For now the song download is only on it’s post on Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/posts/getting-metal-6630820

video.title: Bach Metal

video.description:
Happy New Year! Here's a song with 2016 notes.
The song is titled "Máthair"

Song download (and other stuff) exclusive to Patreon: http://www.patreon.com/RobScallon

How I created a 2016 note song:
-First I wrote a repeating fingerpicking pattern with 36 notes per measure.
-Then structured a song with it to have 56 measures. 36*56=2016
-Then I added a bit of variance to the ending to bring the song to a nice close.
-Then I filmed it and threw it into the internet.

I also tabbed out the song in GuitarPro to be sure.
Tab: https://www.ultimate-guitar.com/search.php?search_type=title&order=&value=scallon+2016

Tab: http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/search.php?search_type=title&value=Scallon+picklet

The song is based around a technique I've been referring to as "picklets." A downstroke/upstroke to a hammered on note, it's a very efficient way to create a triplet. I should have a proper lesson video on it and the song soon. The name of the song is also a nod to now disbanded Chicago Math-Rock band Piglet.

Filmed at Chicago Music Exchange.

tab: http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/search.php?search_type=title&value=envy+scallon

Maybe 2 weeks ago I was really excited to announce an endorsement from Schecter guitars. This was the first thing I asked about "Can I get a 9 string?" I got it in the mail and have been playing it since. It goes down to a C#, making it a step and a half lower then a standard 4 string bass. The biggest criticism I hear about the instrument is that it's taking the whole chug chug 0000 thing to far. I didn't want to write something in the style just yet, I'm sure I'll have fun with that later though. I wanted to write a tune that's heavy and aggressive but also utilizes the instruments full range. So here's what I came up with. Lots of fast riffs and huge stretches. The name is in tribute to a local band from back in my high school days called Jerome.

So the Fender Lone Star & Roadhouse Strats have been around for ages & ages, but in 2013 Fender have given them a makeover. With a new 70s inspired look, new colours & most importantly new pickup options the Lone Star & the Roadhouse Strats have really re-invented themselves.

Want to see all the colours & specs??? Go here http://www.andertons.co.uk/blog/guitars/fender-deluxe-lone-star-roadhouse-strats

As for other gear Chappers is plugged in to a Marshall JVM210 combo & the Captain is using a Fender Hot Rod Deluxe with a Lovepedal E6 Drive pedal

Thanks for watching & can we just say, for the record, Patrick Swayze is great & Roadhouse is one of the finest movies of all time!! Lonestar on the other hand, would not make it in to our top 10 favourite bands - sorry.

Cheers!!

Chappers & the Captain go 60s tastic with the re-issued Bass VI guitars from Fender & Squier. Following in the quirky footsteps of the Pawn Shop range, the Fender Pawn Shop Bass VI is a modded version of the original. However, the Squier Vintage Modified Bass VI is a much closer reproduction in terms of looks & features. 

Anyway... check out the video - hope you enjoy it. Make sure you check out the full spec of each guitar on the Andertons web site - there are several colours to choose from & the price of both guitars (basses?), especially the Squier, has to be seen to be believed!

1st Half....
In Spring 2013 Fender announced they'd be releasing a couple of Mexican made Strats & Teles finished using a nitro cellulose lacquer (just like the expensive USA made Vintage replicas they make). They certainly look a little different, with a deeper shine than a regular polyurethane lacquer, and they are definately going to age in a "prettier" way. But do they sound different.....??? You decide.

For more info on the guitars please go here - http://www.andertons.co.uk/blog/guita...

2nd Half...
We take a look at some pretty new Strats from the Fender Mexican team - these are basically the same as a standard MIM Strat, but with a lovely looking flame maple veneer on the top - thats the only difference, so nuff said about these, but if you want to know more just follow this link - http://www.andertons.co.uk/blog/guita...

Chappers is using an Orange Rockerverb 2x12 combo with no pedals, & Lee is using a Fender hot Rod Deluxe with a LovePedal Eternity E6 drive pedal. You can find more about all these products at www.andertons.co.uk

For those of you who liked the backing track, this was from an album purchased in iTunes. The company is called Jam Discs Backing Tracks & the album is called Blues Rock Backing Tracks - its full of really well recorded tracks - highly recommended!

These two little compact tone machines (we're talking about the amps, not the players!) are the latest arrivals from Blackstar & their excellent True Valve Power (TVP) range. They aren't actually valve amps, but use a great sounding digital circuit that really emulates the way a valve amp works. These amps are great for home use, or for jams & small gigs like a school performance. The TVP series is a little more expensive than most other modelling amps, but Blackstar are trying to appeal to the more discerning player who wants somehting a little better than the rest!

For details on the amps choose one of the following links...
TVP15 - http://www.andertons.co.uk/combo-amps/pid25032/cid691/blackstar-id15tvp-true-valve-power-15w-combo-amp.asp
TVP30 - http://www.andertons.co.uk/combo-amps/pid25031/cid691/blackstar-id30tvp-true-valve-power-30w-combo-amp.asp

The surprise came when Chappers plugged in the little 22w Sensor 1x12 combo (also available in 35w, 50w & 100w versions). We were expecting a nice clean sound & a crunchy dirt channel - what we weren't expecting was an amp that could melt faces & move mountains with its gain channel! Greetings from Chappers & the Captain - hope you enjoyed the little blues jam at the beginning of this video! We're both playing the new Studio Pro Plus combos from Two Rock - whilst they don't replace the original Studio Pro, they have added a few new features to the popular Studio Pro - bigger cabinet, expansion control & built in tremelo. Chappers is playing the 22w & I'm playing the 35w (although you can buy these as heads & also in 50w & 100w versions too!). These make great clean, jazz, blues, & mild rock amps - quiet enough for home, loud enough for a small/medium gig & small enough to go on the front seat of your 2 seater sports car! Wanna know more about these super cool amps? Go here - http://www.andertons.co.uk/blog/guita...

In terms of the other stuff we're using in this demo... Chappers has a Chapman CAP10 guitar & a Keely Red Dirt pedal, and I have a Fender MIM Standard Strat with Flame Top & a LovePedal E6 drive pedal. You can find out more about any of this equipment by going to www.andertons.co.uk

Chappers and the Captain check out the latest range of guitar pedals from Option 5 FX in the USA. The Option 5 range includes a great drive pedal, a juicy phaser, a straight up buffer, a naughty fuzz pedal, plus a really interesting dual delay & an SRV inspired rotary simulator. To find out more about the pedals choose one of the following links...
Bump Buffer/Boost - http://www.andertons.co.uk/compact-pedals/pid28454/cid692/option-5-destination-bump-guitar-effects-pedal.asp
Overdrive II - http://www.andertons.co.uk/compact-pedals/pid28456/cid692/option-5-destination-overdrive-ii-guitar-effects-pedal.asp
Phaser - http://www.andertons.co.uk/compact-pedals/pid28457/cid692/option-5-destination-phaser-guitar-effects-pedal.asp
Delay - http://www.andertons.co.uk/compact-pedals/pid28455/cid692/option-5-destination-delay-x2-guitar-effects-pedal.asp
Rotary Simulator - http://www.andertons.co.uk/compact-pedals/pid28458/cid692/option-5-destination-rotation-guitar-effects-pedal.asp
Fuzz - http://www.andertons.co.uk/compact-pedals/pid28459/cid692/option-5-destination-square-tone-fuzz-guitar-effects-pedal.asp
Amps used are a Marshall JVM 205C & a Fender Hot Rod Deluxe, plus we're using the aweseom new Hot Stone Deluxe multi power supply from Decibel 11, all of which can be purchased from you know where!
video.title: Option 5 Guitar FX Pedal Review of the Range - Highlights

video.description:
Please visit http://www.andertons.co.uk/audio-solutions/pid25466/cid729/palmer-pga04-speaker-simulator-with-loadbox-124-8-ohm-version.asp for more info on the Palmer Speaker Simulator

Rob and Lee demonstrate the latest Palmer Speaker Simulator and compare to the famous PDI-03. They also explain how it can take the place of a traditional guitar cab can if you want to get the best tones out of your amp without any volume.

For the Full Video please visit. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qtypIzTx0t4
video.title: Palmer Speaker Simulator PDI-03 v PGA04 - How does it sound compared to a Cab? Highlights

video.description:
My riff for #RiffsAndBeards2 Riff Contest
Tuning: Drop C

I think this contest was a really cool idea. It forced you to stay within the confines of 130 bpm and to not change the drum pattern at all, which, for me, really brought out a bunch of ideas and almost a full song. I'll definitely be using this riff for a future Shadowless song :D Hope you all enjoy it, let me know what you think!

Check out Fluff's Channel and the contest:

video.title: What A Feeling from Flashdance Meets Metal w/ Ola Englund

video.description:
Hi everyone!

So if you dont know, this past weekend was the NAMM show. Held right here in my hometown of Anaheim, California. And let me tell ya, it was nuts...and it was raining haha. My schedule for after the show is basically a reset. Sometimes it's really nice to just play a cover and reset everything. Journey and the Sopranos have always been a big part of my life. The Sopranos is one of my favorite shows of all time and I could talk about it all day, seriously haha. And I grew up on Journey thanks to my parents. So here we are! Thanks again to my good buddy Rob for hopping on once again for all our entertainment. IMO, he absolutely killed this one just like the rest of em. Be sure to give him a visit and say hi :)

On my mutha's eyes,

E

https://www.youtube.com/user/LundgrenRob

Hi all!

Pretty easy enough, all my friends were doing it so I did it too haha. It's been a good while since I covered a pop tune so I figured we'd give it a shot. So many great covers out there (ten second songs, leo/frog leap, cole rolland) but Rob and I wanted to go for a speedy power metal tone for this one. And just an excuse to dress up as the Joker bc why not. I'm not trying to go for any cosplay awards haha just having some fun. Thanks so much for everything! It means the world. Big ups to my beautiful Momo for getting my face on and big ups to Rob for completely nailing what I sent him :)

Ha ha ha

E
